{
  "id": "474",
  "name": "Use of Function with Inconsistent Implementations",
  "abstraction": "Base",
  "structure": "Simple",
  "status": "Draft",
  "description": "The code uses a function that has inconsistent implementations across operating systems and versions.",
  "extended_description": "\n            \u003cxhtml:p\u003eThe use of inconsistent implementations can cause changes in behavior when the code is ported or built under a different environment than the programmer expects, which can lead to security problems in some cases.\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n            \u003cxhtml:p\u003eThe implementation of many functions varies by platform, and at times, even by different versions of the same platform. Implementation differences can include:\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n            \u003cxhtml:div style=\"margin-left:10px;\"\u003e\n               \u003cxhtml:ul\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:li\u003eSlight differences in the way parameters are interpreted leading to inconsistent results.\u003c/xhtml:li\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:li\u003eSome implementations of the function carry significant security risks.\u003c/xhtml:li\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:li\u003eThe function might not be defined on all platforms.\u003c/xhtml:li\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:li\u003eThe function might change which return codes it can provide, or change the meaning of its return codes.\u003c/xhtml:li\u003e\n               \u003c/xhtml:ul\u003e\n            \u003c/xhtml:div\u003e\n         ",
